              ],
              "free_text": [
                " Target thickness was 151.1 mg/cm2"
              ]
            }
          ],
          "ERR-ANALYS": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": {
                "heading": "ERR-S",
                "minimum_value": null,
                "maximum_value": null,
                "correlation_property": null
              },
              "free_text": [
                " Statistical errors (from 5 to 10% for the",
                " forward and from 5 up to more than 20% for the",
                " backward angles)"
              ]
            },
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": {
                "heading": "ERR-SYS",
                "minimum_value": null,
                "maximum_value": null,
                "correlation_property": null
              },
              "free_text": [
                " Systematic uncertainties were estimated to",
                " be about 15% and stems from several  contributions:",
                " the  energy  calibration of the detectors (due to",
                " extrapolation), the effect on the cross section",
                " due to the error in the determination of the",
                " end-point energy, the calibration constant of the",
                " monitoring device, and the target thickness",
                " homogeneity."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "COMMENT": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                "The differential cross section for the",
                " 160(gamma,p0)15N reaction has been investigated  at",
                " photon energies Eg between 33 and 69 MeV using  a",
                " bremsstrahlung beam; angular distributions at",
                " laboratory angles of  30, 45, 60, 75, 90, and 120",
                " degree were extracted  from the tip region of  the",
                " photoproton spectra when stepping the end-point in",
                " 4 MeV intervals. The data  were compared with",
                " calculations based on a self-consistent microscopic",
                "  approach."
              ]
            }
          ],
